the palestinian keffiyeh ( arabic : كوفية , koofiyyeh ) is a gender-neutral chequered black and white scarf that is usually worn around the neck or head .   the palestinian keffiyeh has become a symbol of palestinian nationalism , dating back to the 1936 – 1939 arab revolt in palestine .   outside of the middle east and north africa , the keffiyeh first gained popularity among activists supporting the palestinians in the conflict with israel and is an icon of " palestinian solidarity " .